text.tspan: Overflow tabs go into a menu
• New tab button is disconnected from the tab bar.
• It takes a click to access overflow tabs - could feel awkward, like work.
• No way to shift the entire sequence of visible tabs.
• No way to get an overview of all open tabs.
• It's a lot of buttons to have in the tab bar.
• You should always be able to see the focused tab.
• Pan buttons ideally wouldn't be needed if there's multitouch/a scroll wheel.
• Jakub won't like all the lines.
• Awkward relationship between stacked tabs and pan arrows - in this example, pressing left would expand to the right of the active tab.

flowRoot.flowPara: Pan overflow tabs, rather than put them in a menu.
Always keep the current tab visible, by stacking open tabs against it.
Overflow tabs bunch up, clicking a bunch expands it. Also known as, the SUPER ACCORDION.1

text.tspan: • Need to ensure that bunched tabs are big enough to click on comfortably - could be awkward when there are only a small number of overflow tabs.
